stories.text:
I'm a full-stack dev by DNA, but for the past half a decade I've been thinking / focussing on the front-end. Front-end saw some huge changes during these years like Angular/Ember slowly phasing out, Component based code architecture and functional paradigms in front-end stores, code bundling techniques, etc.

Curious how the scene is in the server-side world? What recent developments happened and how good/bad are they?

Beryllium, a Singapore based fintech firm that is building a stock market for athletes is hiring for multiple roles, backend tech lead, senior backend engineer, front end engineers. Beryllium is used by over 200K users, and has raised a $3M Pre-Series A round.

Send resumes to jobs@sixergame.com!

Location Singapore timezone is preferred, but all locations and remote work!
